                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 29: Tata Motors will hike the price of the Nano by about Rs 9,000 with effect from November 1 to offset rising input costs. This is the second time that the company has increased the price of the car. In July, Tata Motors had raised the price by 3-4 per cent, translating into a hike ranging between Rs 3,700 and Rs 6,894 (ex-showroom, Delhi).                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 29: Concerned over delays in environment clearance to Poscos Rs 54,000-crore project in India, steel minister Virbhadra Singh said all hurdles should be removed expeditiously. The demand for speeding up the proposal was in view of the new steelmaking technology it promised to bring into the country.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 29: Samsung has forayed into the Indian tablet PC market with the launch of Android-powered Galaxy Tab, priced at Rs 38,000.                                                                                                                          
